[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Device Hardware & Physical Operation

[TEST]
UID: TEST-1
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/04/2026
TITLE: Visual Dose Indicators and Bin Identification
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device with an active medication schedule that includes at least one AM dose and one PM dose for the current day. The device is powered on and connected to Wi-Fi.

Steps:
1. Observe the physical device at the scheduled AM dose time.
2. Verify that the LED indicator for the correct AM bin (the bin mapped to today's AM slot, labelled with the Sun symbol) is blinking green.
3. Verify no other bin LEDs are blinking green.
4. Without opening the bin, wait 15 minutes past the scheduled AM dose time.
5. Verify that the AM bin LED transitions from blinking green to solid red, indicating the dose has not been taken within the alert window.
6. Open the AM bin (simulating a late dose).
7. Verify the AM bin LED changes from solid red to solid green immediately upon the bin opening.
8. Observe the device at the scheduled PM dose time.
9. Verify that only the LED for the correct PM bin (labelled with the Moon symbol) is blinking green.
10. Open the PM bin within the first 15 minutes of the scheduled time.
11. Verify the PM bin LED changes to solid green immediately upon opening.
12. Cross-reference the bin indicated by the device LED against the physical day-of-week and Sun/Moon labels printed on the device lid/body.



Acceptance Criteria:
- Only the correct bin LED activates (blinking green) at the correct scheduled time.
- If a dose is not taken within 15 minutes of the scheduled time, the bin LED changes from blinking green to solid red.
- Opening a bin (whether on time or late) immediately changes the LED to solid green.
- The bin indicated by the LED matches the physical Sun/Moon and day-of-week label.
<<<
