[TEST]
UID: TEST-2
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/04/2026
TITLE: Physical Pill Loading Procedure
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A device with an empty organizer tray. A supply of two clearly distinguishable types of test pills (e.g., vitamin tablets of two different colors or sizes). The device is powered on.

Steps:
1. Inspect each of the 14 bins to confirm they are physically distinct, individually separated, and clearly labelled (day of week + AM/PM symbol).
2. Load test pills of type A into the 7 AM (Sun) bins, placing 1–2 pills per bin.
3. Load test pills of type B into the 7 PM (Moon) bins, placing 1–2 pills per bin.
4. Re-open the device lid and verify that the pills loaded into each bin remain in that bin without having spilled into adjacent bins.
5. Verify that pills from AM bins have not mixed with pills in PM bins.
6. Confirm that all 14 bins are accessible and can be opened with fingers alone.

Acceptance Criteria:
- All 14 bins are distinct, individually accessible, and labelled.
- Pills loaded into a bin do not spill into adjacent bins under normal handling.
- AM and PM bin contents remain physically separate.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: UN-102
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST]
UID: TEST-3
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/05/2026
TITLE: Battery Level Monitoring and Critical Power Alerts
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device with the mobile app installed and logged in. A bench power supply capable of providing stable DC voltage in the 3.2V–3.7V range, connected to the device's battery terminals via appropriate connectors.

Steps — FULL state (normal operation):
1. Set the bench power supply to 3.60 V and connect to the device battery terminals.
2. Power on the device. Open the mobile app and navigate to the device status screen.
3. Verify the device operates normally with no battery warning displayed in the app.

Steps — LOW threshold (3.50 V):
4. While the device is running, gradually lower the supply voltage to 3.50 V (between 3.45 V and 3.55 V).
5. Wait for at least 10 consecutive ULP poll cycles to allow the level debounce logic to settle (approximately 30 seconds).
6. Verify that the mobile app displays a distinct low battery status indicator.

Steps — CRITICAL threshold (3.40 V):
7. Lower the supply voltage to 3.40 V (below 3.45 V).
8. Wait for at least 10 consecutive ULP poll cycles to allow the shutoff threshold to be confirmed.
9. Verify that the mobile app displays a distinct battery critical low status indicator.

Acceptance Criteria:
- At supply voltage > 3.55 V: no battery warning is displayed.
- At supply voltage between 3.45 V and 3.55 V: a distinct LOW battery warning is displayed in the mobile app and on the device.
- At supply voltage below 3.45V: a distinct CRITICAL battery warning is displayed in the mobile app and on the device.
- No continuous battery percentage is displayed; only discrete status levels are reported.
<<<
