  VALUE: UN-205
  ROLE: Verifies
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: UN-206
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST]
UID: TEST-4
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/05/2026
TITLE: Power Loss State Persistence
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device with an active medication schedule configured (e.g., daily AM and PM doses). The device has been running normally and has synchronized with the backend within the last hour.

Steps:
1. Note the current device state: active schedule, state, and any pending dose indicators.
2. Disconnect power from the device (remove batteries or unplug if applicable).
3. Wait at least 30 seconds to simulate a meaningful power interruption.
4. Restore power to the device.
5. Observe the device boot sequence.
6. Verify that after booting, the device automatically resumes displaying the active medication schedule without any user interaction.
7. Verify that the scheduled dose indicators activate at the correct times following the restart (observe through the next scheduled dose time).
8. Verify that no reconfiguration prompt or setup wizard is shown.
9. Open the mobile app and confirm the device reconnects to the backend and resumes synchronization without manual intervention.

Acceptance Criteria:
- The device restores its prior operating state automatically after power is restored.
- No user reconfiguration is required.
- Scheduled dose alerts resume at the correct times.
- The device reconnects and synchronizes with the backend automatically.
<<<
