TITLE: Medication Scheduling

[TEST]
UID: TEST-5
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/04/2026
TITLE: Daily Medication Schedule Configuration
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device with no active schedule. User is logged into the mobile app as the Primary User (Patient).

Steps — Once-daily use verification:
1. Open the mobile app and navigate to the schedule configuration screen for the device.
2. Configure a twice-daily schedule (the app requires both an AM and a PM time) with an AM dose time and a PM dose time for all 7 days of the week.
3. Assign a start day (e.g., Monday) and confirm the schedule.
4. Load pills into only the AM (Sun) bins. Leave all PM (Moon) bins empty.
5. At the scheduled AM dose time for one day, open only the AM bin. Do not open the PM bin.
6. Verify the AM dose is recorded as "Taken" in the adherence history.
7. Verify the adherence record for that day reflects at least one taken dose, demonstrating the device can support a once-daily dosing pattern even within a twice-daily schedule.

Steps — Twice-daily schedule and label alignment:
8. With the twice-daily schedule active, verify that the app maps AM doses to Sun-labelled bins and PM doses to Moon-labelled bins for each day of the week.
9. Verify that the digital schedule displayed in the app aligns with the physical Sun/Moon and day-of-week labels on the device.
10. Attempt to assign a PM dose to the same bin slot as an existing AM dose on the same day.
11. Verify the system enforces that AM (Sun) bins are scheduled before PM (Moon) bins and does not allow reversed assignment.
12. Save the schedule and confirm it is applied to the device within 5 minutes (indicated by all lights on the device blinking green).

Acceptance Criteria:
- A once-daily dosing pattern is achievable on the device; opening only the AM bin each day is recorded as a taken event.
- The digital schedule always aligns with Sun (AM) and Moon (PM) physical labels for each day.
- The system prevents scheduling AM doses after PM doses within the same calendar day.
- The configured schedule is successfully applied to the device.
<<<
