[TEST]
UID: TEST-6
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/04/2026
TITLE: Medication Cycle Management and Fill Confirmation
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device with a 7-day active schedule that has been completed (all doses for the current week have been taken or the cycle end date has been reached). User is logged into the mobile app as the Primary User.

Steps:
1. Allow the device to reach the end of its active schedule cycle (all 7 days elapsed, or all scheduled doses exhausted).
2. Verify the device needs a reload by observing all lights flashing orange and the proper indication in the mobile app.
3. Open a single bin on the device and observe the LEDs change.
4. Load medication into every bin indicated red, opening and closing the door. Observe the LED change to green.
5. Complete the reload/fill confirmation flow by completing this process for all bins on the device to transition the device to a new cycle.
6. Verify that the adherence tracking is reset: all bins for the new cycle are shown as "pending" or "not yet taken."
7. Verify that the previous cycle's adherence history remains accessible in the adherence history screen.
8. Verify the device LED indicators and app are now aligned to the first dose of the new cycle.

Acceptance Criteria:
- At the end of a cycle, the device indicates that the bins should be reloaded.
- A new cycle can be initiated after the previous cycle is complete.
- Fill confirmation resets adherence tracking for the new cycle.
- Prior cycle adherence history is preserved and viewable.
- Device LEDs and app correctly indicate the first dose of the new cycle.
<<<
