[TEST]
UID: TEST-7
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/05/2026
TITLE: Mid-Cycle Schedule Adjustment
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device in the middle of an active 7-day cycle (e.g., 3 days completed, 4 days remaining). At least 2 doses have already been recorded as "taken" in the current cycle. User is logged into the mobile app as the Primary User.

Steps:
1. Open the mobile app and navigate to the schedule configuration screen.
2. Note the current adherence records for the days already completed in the cycle (e.g., Day 1 AM: Taken, Day 1 PM: Taken, Day 2 AM: Taken).
3. Modify the schedule for the remaining days of the cycle (e.g., remove the PM dose for the remaining days, or change the dose time).
4. Save the modified schedule.
5. Verify that the adherence records for doses already taken (Days 1–2 in this example) are unchanged.
6. Verify that the schedule for the remaining days reflects the new configuration.
7. Observe the device and verify that the LEDs for the next upcoming dose align with the updated schedule.
8. Verify that no previously recorded adherence event has been altered or deleted.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Schedule changes during an active cycle apply only to upcoming doses.
- Previously recorded adherence events are preserved without modification.
- The device LEDs correctly reflect the updated upcoming schedule.
<<<
