[TEST]
UID: TEST-8
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/04/2026
TITLE: Automated Dose Detection and Classification
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device with an active schedule. The device is loaded with pills and connected to Wi-Fi. The mobile app is installed and logged in as the Primary User.

Steps:
1. At the scheduled AM dose time for today, open the correct AM bin within the first 15 minutes of the scheduled dose time.
2. Wait up to 10 seconds, then open the mobile app and navigate to the adherence tracking screen.
3. Verify that the dose event for today's AM bin is automatically recorded as "Taken."
4. At the scheduled PM dose time, wait until 15 minutes past the scheduled time without opening the bin.
5. Verify that the PM bin LED has changed from blinking green to solid red.
6. Open the mobile app and verify that the PM dose event is recorded as "Missed."
6. On a different day, open the correct bin 1 minute before the dose window closes (i.e., late but within the window).
7. Verify the dose is recorded as "Taken".
8. On another day, open the correct bin after the dose window has closed but before the next scheduled dose.
9. Verify the dose is recorded as "Taken."
10. Verify that the adherence screen clearly displays the actual taken time.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Opening a bin during the correct dose window is automatically recorded as a taken event.
- Taken and missed doses are distinctly labeled in the adherence record with the time.
- The automated detection requires no manual user input.
<<<
