[TEST]
UID: TEST-9
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/08/2026
TITLE: Remote Dose Notifications and Preference Control
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device with an active daily schedule. The mobile app is installed on a test smartphone with push notifications enabled. User is logged in as the Primary User. A second test smartphone is available for Caregiver testing.

Steps:
1. Open the mobile app and navigate to notification settings.
2. Enable "Upcoming Dose" notifications and disable "Missed Dose" notifications.
3. Wait for a scheduled dose time.
4. Verify that a push notification is received on the smartphone at or near the scheduled dose time, indicating which dose is due.
5. Allow the dose window to close without opening the bin.
6. Verify that no "Missed Dose" notification is received (since it was disabled).
7. Return to notification settings and enable "Missed Dose" notifications.
8. Allow the next dose window to close without opening the bin.
9. Verify that a "Missed Dose" push notification is received.
10. Repeat the steps for the caregiver account.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Dose-due notifications are received at the scheduled dose time when enabled.
- Missed dose notifications are received only when that notification type is enabled.
- Notification preferences can be independently configured for each user (Patient and Caregiver).
- Disabling a notification type suppresses that notification type.
<<<
