[TEST]
UID: TEST-10
RUN_RESULT: Blocked
TITLE: Manual Adherence Record Correction
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device with an active schedule. At least one dose event has been recorded (either a false positive: bin opened but pill not taken, or a false negative: pill taken without the device detecting it). User is logged into the mobile app as the Primary User.

Steps:
1. Open the mobile app and navigate to the adherence history screen.
2. Locate a "Taken" event that was a false positive (bin was opened but the pill was not actually taken).
3. Select the event and choose the option to mark it as "Not Taken" or correct the record.
4. Confirm the change and verify the event is updated in the adherence history.
5. Locate a dose slot that is recorded as "Missed" (a false negative where the pill was actually taken without device detection).
6. Select the event and choose the option to mark it as "Taken" or add a manual taken record.
7. Confirm the change and verify the event is updated as "Taken" in the adherence history.
8. Verify that a correction timestamp or notation indicating the record was manually modified is visible on the corrected entry.

Acceptance Criteria:
- False positive "Taken" events can be corrected to "Not Taken."
- False negative "Missed" events can be corrected to "Taken."
- Corrected entries are indicated as manually modified in the record.
