[TEST]
UID: TEST-12
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/06/2026
TITLE: Device Synchronization and Connection Status
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device connected to Wi-Fi. The mobile app is installed and logged in as the Primary User. A bin is currently scheduled to be taken and is blinking green.

Steps:
1. Open the mobile app and confirm the device is displayed (no error indicating the device is offline).
2. Make a configuration change in the mobile app by changing the time zone or schedule.
3. Wait up to 15 minutes and verify the change is reflected on the device by observing the device LEDs flash green for 5 seconds.
4. Open a bin on the device (not the one currently indicating to be taken) to trigger a state change.
5. Observe the device display indicates the bin is opened in the app within 10 seconds.
6. Disconnect the device from Wi-Fi (disable the Wi-Fi network or move device out of range).
7. Observe the mobile app and verify it shows the device as "Offline" or displays a connection-lost indicator within one hour.
8. Open and close the scheduled bin on the offline device.
9. Reconnect the device to Wi-Fi.
10. Verify the app displays the dose as taken.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Configuration changes made in the app are applied to the device within 15 minutes.
- Bin-open state change events appear in the app within 10 seconds when the device is online.
- The app shows a distinct "Offline" indicator when the device cannot communicate with the backend.
- Events recorded while offline are synchronized to the app once connectivity is restored.
<<<
