[TEST]
UID: TEST-13
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/06/2026
TITLE: Offline Autonomous Operation
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device with an active medication schedule and loaded pills. Device is currently connected to Wi-Fi.

Steps:
1. Confirm the device is operating normally: LEDs activate at the correct scheduled dose time.
2. Disconnect the device from Wi-Fi by physically removing it from Wi-Fi range.
3. Verify the device is no longer able to communicate with the backend (app shows device offline).
4. Wait for the next scheduled dose time while the device is offline.
5. Verify that the device LED indicator activates for the correct bin at the scheduled dose time, without any internet connection.
6. Open the correct bin and verify the LED changes to solid green.
7. Verify that the device has locally logged the bin-open event(this can be confirmed after reconnection by checking the adherence history reflects the event).
8. Verify that the device continues to activate LEDs for subsequent scheduled doses while still offline.

Acceptance Criteria:
- The device executes the loaded medication schedule (activates LED alerts) without any internet connection.
- Bin-open events are logged locally while offline.
- Local event logs are retained for synchronization upon reconnection.
<<<
