[TEST]
UID: TEST-15
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/06/2026
TITLE: Account Creation, Unique Identity, and Secure Login
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: Access to the mobile app on a test device. A valid email address for Patient account creation and a second email for Caregiver account creation. No prior accounts exist for these email addresses.

Steps:
1. Open the app and select "Create Account".
2. Enter credentials for a new Patient account (email + password meeting complexity requirements). Submit. Enter verification code from email.
3. Verify the account is created and the user is directed to the main app screen.
4. Log out of the Patient account.
5. Repeat steps 1–4 for a new Caregiver account using a different email address.
6. Log out of the Caregiver account.
7. Attempt to create a third account using the same email address as the Patient account.
8. Verify the system rejects the duplicate and displays an appropriate error.
9. Log into the Patient account using the correct credentials. Verify access is granted.
10. Log into the Caregiver account using the correct credentials. Verify access is granted.
11. Attempt to log in with an incorrect password for the Patient account.
12. Verify access is denied and an appropriate error is displayed.
13. Verify that each account has a unique user identifier assigned in the administrative dashboard.
14. Attempt to access a protected screen (e.g., device dashboard) without being logged in (log out first, then navigate directly).
15. Verify the system redirects to the login screen and denies access.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Patient and Caregiver accounts can be created with unique credentials.
- Duplicate email addresses are rejected.
- Login with correct credentials succeeds; incorrect credentials are denied.
- Each account has a unique, permanent user identifier.
- Unauthenticated access to protected resources is denied.
<<<
