[TEST]
UID: TEST-17
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/08/2026
TITLE: Account Closure and Data Privacy
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A Patient account and device with some adherence history. A Caregiver account associated with that device.

Steps:
1. Log into the Patient account.
2. Navigate to account settings and initiate account closure.
3. Confirm the closure request.
4. Verify the account can no longer be used to log in.
5. Verify that the Patient's personally identifying information (name, email, contact details) has been removed or anonymized.
6. Verify via web dashboard that the historical adherence data associated with the now-closed account is still present but no longer linked to any personally identifying information.
7. Attempt to log into the closed account and verify access is denied.
8. Log into the Caregiver account and verify the Caregiver can no longer access the device previously associated with the closed Patient account.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Account closure removes or anonymizes all PII for the user.
- Historical health/adherence data is retained in anonymized form.
- The closed account cannot be used to log in.
- Caregivers lose access to the device when the Primary User account is closed.
