[TEST]
UID: TEST-18
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/06/2026
TITLE: Device Provisioning via Mobile App
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device assigned to a different Patient account. A Patient account on the mobile app. A Wi-Fi network with known credentials. Physical access to the device.

Steps:
1. Log into the Patient account on the mobile app.
2. Navigate to "Add Device" or "Provision New Device" in the app.
3. Follow the in-app provisioning wizard.
4. When prompted, enter the Wi-Fi SSID and password for the test Wi-Fi network.
5. Confirm that the provisioning process requires physical proximity (e.g., Bluetooth pairing) to verify physical possession.
6. Complete the provisioning wizard.
7. Verify the device connects to Wi-Fi and communicates with the backend (app shows device as online).
8. Verify the Patient account that performed provisioning is automatically designated as the Primary User of the device by changing the schedule of it.
9. Verify the device appears in the Patient's device list in the app.
10. Attempt to provision the same device again without first deprovisioning it.
11. Verify the system does not allow provisioning.
12. Sign in with the original Patient account and attempt to change the schedule. Observe the schedule change is not accepted by the system.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Device can be provisioned entirely through the mobile app.
- Provisioning requires physical interaction with the device (possession verification).
- The provisioning user is automatically designated as the Primary User.
- The device appears in the user's device list after provisioning.
- Re-provisioning revokes old credentials and issues new ones.
