TITLE: Device Re-Provisioning and Data Transfer
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: Patient account with one provisioned device (Device A) that has an active schedule, a device nickname, and several weeks of adherence data. A second unprovisioned device (Device B) is available.

Steps — Re-Provisioning Existing Device (Preserve Data):
1. Log into the Patient account. Note Device A's nickname, schedule, and a sample of adherence history.
2. Navigate to "Add Device" and re-provision Device A (using the same physical device) through the provisioning wizard.
3. After re-provisioning completes, navigate to Device A's settings.
4. Verify the device nickname is preserved.
5. Verify the active schedule is preserved.
6. Verify the adherence history is preserved.

Steps — Transfer to New Device:
7. Navigate to "Add Device" and begin provisioning Device B.
8. When prompted, select the option to transfer configuration and data from Device A.
9. Complete the provisioning of Device B.
10. Verify Device B has the same nickname, schedule, and adherence history as Device A had before the transfer.
11. Verify Device B appears in the device list and Device A is either removed or shows as transferred.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Re-provisioning an existing device preserves its configuration, schedule, and adherence history.
- Provisioning a new device with a data transfer copies the configuration, schedule, and adherence records from the source device.
