[TEST]
UID: TEST-26
RUN_RESULT: Passed
RUN_BY: Brendan Heinonen
RUN_DATE: 05/06/2026
TITLE: Central Backend Platform and API Connectivity
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A provisioned device. Bruno test client. AWS Console IoT Core MQTT test client. MQTTx CLI.

Steps:
1. With the device online, observe the device state report on the appropriate MQTT topic.
2. Confirm API requests without a valid user JWT token to the backend are rejected using Bruno.
4. Confirm API requests with a valid JWT token, but to a different, unauthorized device to the backend are rejected.
5. Confirm API requests with a valid JWT token to an authorized device to the backend are accepted.
6. Trigger a state change on the device (e.g., open a bin) and verify the payload changes in the MQTT client.
7. Use the MQTTx CLI to connect to MQTT over WebSocket with JWT credentials. Attempt to publish to the device state topic. Ensure the connection is terminated due to unauthorized request.

Acceptance Criteria:
- The mobile app communicates with the backend via a secure API.
- All API traffic is encrypted in transit (HTTPS/TLS).
- Both device and user app requests are authenticated.
- State changes on the device are reflected via MQTT.
<<<
