TITLE: Trial Protocol Definition and Participant Management
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: A Researcher account with ownership of a clinical trial (Trial T001). A pool of test Patient accounts. At least two unprovisioned test devices.

Steps:
1. Log into the Researcher account on the researcher portal.
2. Navigate to Trial T001 protocol settings.
3. Define a default medication schedule (e.g., once daily AM dose, 7-day cycle) as the default protocol configuration.
4. Save the protocol configuration.
5. Navigate to the participant management screen for Trial T001.
6. Authorize Patient Account A for enrollment in Trial T001 (issue an enrollment code or invitation).
7. Attempt to have Patient Account B (not authorized) enroll in Trial T001. Verify the enrollment is rejected.
8. Navigate to the device management screen for Trial T001.
9. Designate Device X as exclusive to Trial T001 (associate the device with the trial).
10. Navigate to the participant/device overview screen and verify that both the participant list and the device list for Trial T001 are visible, including devices not yet associated with any participant.
11. After Patient A enrolls (using their Patient account to accept the invitation), assign Subject ID "P001" to Patient A from the researcher portal.
12. Verify Patient A is listed under Subject ID "P001" in the Trial T001 participant list.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Researchers can define and save a default protocol configuration for a trial.
- Only authorized participants can enroll in the trial; unauthorized enrollment is rejected.
- Devices can be designated as exclusive to a trial by the researcher.
- The researcher can view all participants and all devices associated with the trial.
- Each participant can be assigned a unique Subject ID (pseudonymous identifier).
