[TEST]
UID: TEST-36
RUN_RESULT: Failed
TITLE: Trial Monitoring, Analytics, and Data Access Integrity
STATEMENT: >>>
Prerequisites: Trial T001 has at least 5 enrolled participants. Adherence events include a mix of Missed and Taken, and periods where devices were offline (unknown). A Researcher account with access to Trial T001. A second Researcher account with access only to Trial T002.

Steps:
1. Log into the Researcher account (with Trial T001 access) on the researcher portal.
2. Navigate to the Trial T001 adherence monitoring dashboard.
3. Verify that adherence records for all enrolled Trial T001 participants are visible.
4. Verify the dashboard differentiates between "known" dose events (device checked in and confirmed taken/missed) and "unknown" statuses (device has not checked in and no status is available).
5. Navigate to the aggregate compliance/analytics view.
6. Verify a high-level adherence trend summary is displayed.
7. Log out and log into the second Researcher account (Trial T002 only).
8. Attempt to access Trial T001's participant adherence data.
9. Verify access is denied.
10. Verify that the Trial T002 researcher cannot see any adherence data belonging to Trial T001 participants, even if some patients are enrolled in both trials.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Researchers can monitor adherence for all Trial Participants in their trial.
- The dashboard distinguishes "known" events from "unknown" status (device not checked in).
- High-level aggregate adherence trends are available.
- Researchers can only access data from trials they are authorized for; cross-trial data access is denied.
<<<
RESULT_STRING: >>>
Failed because researcher accounts don't work, need to investigate
<<<
